   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_unknown_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>new, and perfectly true idea - and in<lb/>
               this age of repetition <add>&amp; deception</add>, a perfectly new &amp;<lb/>
               perfectly true idea is so rare that it is <choice>
                  <orig>suffi<lb/>
                  cient</orig>
                  <reg>sufficient</reg>
               </choice> to make a reputation - <del>The</del>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I allude to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ConsB1">M. B. Constant</persName>s remark<lb/>
               that despotism has produced in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#FR">France</placeName>
               <lb/>
               a power which has become more than<lb/>
               a match for itself - It has produced<lb/>
               that system of industry which render<lb/>
               men independant of court favor &amp;<lb/>
               which creates that <hi rend="underline">substantive</hi> body of<lb/>
               public opinion which can stand alone<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ConsB1">M. Constant</persName> might much improve<lb/>
               himself as a speaker &amp; a writer by studying<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BurkE1">Burke</persName> whom he more resembles in<lb/>
               manner than any of our speakers <damage><unclear>or<gap></gap></unclear></damage>
               <lb/>
               writers - <del>But</del> he wants more of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BurkE1">Burke</persName>
               <damage><unclear>'s<gap></gap></unclear></damage>
               <lb/>
               strength and has too much of his ornament <damage><unclear>-<gap></gap></unclear></damage>
               <lb/>
               <add>- too much declamation - too many words - 10 times <damage><gap></gap></damage></add>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>You oblige me much by sending <unclear/>
               <lb/>
               me these tracts which keep me up with<lb/>
               the current of your literature &amp; politics<lb/>
                  For The 2 numbers of your <title ref="./Workography.xml#Revue1">Revue - <choice>
                     <orig>Encyclo-<lb/>
                  pedique</orig>
                     <reg>Encyclopedique</reg>
                  </choice>
               </title> which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParkE1">Madame Belloc</persName> tells me<lb/>
               you have sent to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DeleX1">M Deleports</persName> for me to<lb/>
               come over with her next parcel I thank<lb/>
               you sincerely - My brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd <choice>
                     <orig>Edge-<lb/>
                  worth</orig>
                     <reg>Edgeworth</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> intends to set out from <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName> for<lb/>
               England in a few days &amp; will bring the<lb/>
               books to me - He will call at <persName ref="./Personography.xml#DeleX1">M Deleport</persName>s<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Harvard_604742_unknown_page02.jpg"/>
            <p>With a just sense of your continued<lb/>
               attentions to me</p>
            <closer>I am<lb/>
               <choice>
                  <orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>Dear</reg>
               </choice> Sir Your obliged &amp; grateful<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>a</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Monsieur</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#JullM1">Mons<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Jullien</persName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Rue-d'Enfen-Saint-Michel-18_FR">Rue d'Enfen Saint-Michel, N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. 18</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
